  • limitation

Introduction¶

in this project we will invistigate a dataset for 100k medical appointments in Brazil.¶

this data is based on whether the patients showed up on the appointment that they booked or not with some specific data for each patient such as thier medical reports and diseases¶

  • patientId=Identification of a patient
  • AppointmentID= Identification of each appointment
  • Gender= Male or Female
  • ScheduledDay= The day of the actual appointment
  • AppointmentDay= The day the patient or someone called to book an appointment
  • Age= Age of the patient
  • Neighbourhood= the hospital where the appointment takes place.
  • Scholarship= If the person receives welfare assistance (True of False)
  • Hipertension= True or False
  • Diabetes= True or False
  • Alcoholism = True or False
  • Handicap = True or False
  • SMS -received= messages sent to the patient to verify thier appointments
  • No-show= with values True or False.

Questions for the analysis¶

1.what is the ratio between the patient who showed up and those who didn't?¶

2.Is sending an sms made a progress for showing up on the appointments?¶

3. Is there a correlation between the neighbourhood of the hospital and showing up on thier appointments?¶

4.Does females happens to show up on thier appointments more than males?¶

5.Does the age matter on showing up?¶

6.Is enrolling in brazilllian welfare program has raised number of patients who showed up?¶

7.Is having a chronic disease affect on not showing up on the appointments?¶

8.Is being an alcoholic affects the missed appointments percentage?¶

9.What factors are important for us to know in order to predict if a patient will show up for thier appointments?¶

Conclusions¶

  • most of the patients don't have chronic disease.

  • sending an sms to the patients didn't made much progress for showing up

  • people who showed up are 3 quarters more than the patients who didn't show up, which means that the hospital is making a progress but this analysis should be an indicator for what steps should be made for better outcome.

  • patients who didn't enroll in brazilllian welfare program is higher than the people who enrolled,which means that the welfare didn't make much progress or didn't grap people attention and this should be considerd.

  • showing up in alchoholic patients is more than. the not showing percentage with a huge difference! this should be noticable.

limitation¶

  • No clear chronic correlation between chronic disease and show up and not showing up

  • Couldn't dig dipper in showing up and not showing up by date or years to see the progress

  • Couldn't identify the welfare program whether it's a discount or what to get to know better it's effect on showing or no shwoing up for the patients
